1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,980
[2025 Chungnam location incentive
production support project]

2
00:00:10,860 --> 00:00:13,500
[Woo Jihan]

3
00:00:15,760 --> 00:00:18,340
[Shin Jeongyou]

4
00:00:20,320 --> 00:00:22,600
[Min Dohee]

5
00:00:24,140 --> 00:00:26,680
[Seo Seunghyeon]

6
00:00:30,110 --> 00:00:35,020
[Always Meet Again]

7
00:00:37,650 --> 00:00:38,310
Isn't that

8
00:00:38,460 --> 00:00:39,460
Woojin?

9
00:00:40,170 --> 00:00:41,440
Right. Why is he there?

10
00:00:47,350 --> 00:00:48,350
Hey, Lee Woojin!

11
00:00:48,630 --> 00:00:49,630
Woojin!

12
00:01:23,340 --> 00:01:24,110
Huh?

13
00:01:25,210 --> 00:01:26,070
What happened?

14
00:01:27,980 --> 00:01:29,710
Where'd he go? What's going on?

15
00:01:30,590 --> 00:01:31,590
Jang Hyeseong...

16
00:01:39,720 --> 00:01:45,979
[Episode 8:
Transcend Time]

17
00:01:52,690 --> 00:01:53,690
Are you OK?

18
00:01:59,170 --> 00:02:00,170
Jang Hyeseong...

19
00:02:12,640 --> 00:02:13,250
Hey, Woojin.

20
00:02:13,250 --> 00:02:14,250
Woojin!

21
00:02:19,010 --> 00:02:20,010
Lee Woojin!

22
00:03:01,060 --> 00:03:01,560
[Lee Woojin]

23
00:03:20,750 --> 00:03:21,750
No way.

24
00:03:22,810 --> 00:03:24,270
I came back just like that?

25
00:03:34,140 --> 00:03:36,560
[We're here!]

26
00:03:49,730 --> 00:03:50,920
It wasn't a dream.

27
00:04:11,820 --> 00:04:13,550
[Park Taejun]

28
00:04:14,040 --> 00:04:15,040
Taejun?

29
00:04:19,690 --> 00:04:20,320
Hello?

30
00:04:20,390 --> 00:04:22,089
Hey, the great artist Jang!

31
00:04:22,490 --> 00:04:23,990
Your exhibition is tomorrow.

32
00:04:23,990 --> 00:04:25,190
How's the prep going?

33
00:04:25,710 --> 00:04:26,520
What?

34
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:28,200
My exhibition?

35
00:04:29,470 --> 00:04:30,000
Yeah.

36
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:31,570
What's with that reaction?

37
00:04:32,140 --> 00:04:33,600
Is the prep not going well?

38
00:04:34,860 --> 00:04:35,620
Oh. No, no.

39
00:04:35,650 --> 00:04:36,990
It's going well.

40
00:04:38,690 --> 00:04:39,690
But...

41
00:04:41,960 --> 00:04:44,270
I'm sorry I suddenly disappeared that day.

42
00:04:44,270 --> 00:04:45,130
What?

43
00:04:45,580 --> 00:04:46,510
What do you mean?

44
00:04:47,390 --> 00:04:48,520
I mean, I'm sorry I disappeared

45
00:04:48,520 --> 00:04:50,920
during the break of
my special lecture at your school.

46
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:52,670
What are you talking about?

47
00:04:53,500 --> 00:04:54,790
Are you doing the special lecture?

48
00:04:54,790 --> 00:04:56,360
Didn't you say "never in a million years"?

49
00:04:56,360 --> 00:04:57,760
Did you change your mind?

50
00:04:58,450 --> 00:04:59,100
Huh?

51
00:04:59,320 --> 00:05:00,520
Nice! Then wait for me

52
00:05:01,130 --> 00:05:02,010
to get off work.

53
00:05:02,040 --> 00:05:04,060
Let's talk over some chicken and beer.

54
00:05:04,060 --> 00:05:04,960
I've got to go to class.

55
00:05:04,960 --> 00:05:05,630
See you later.

56
00:05:05,630 --> 00:05:06,630
Hey.

57
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:07,640
Wait! Hey!

58
00:05:14,970 --> 00:05:16,720
Wait, what's going on?

59
00:05:24,570 --> 00:05:27,380
I'll look for it and get back to you ASAP.

60
00:06:00,630 --> 00:06:01,630
Woojin!

61
00:06:02,760 --> 00:06:03,760
Hey, Lee Woojin!

62
00:06:07,860 --> 00:06:08,860
Jang Hyeseong?

63
00:06:10,300 --> 00:06:11,300
Wait right there!

64
00:06:36,940 --> 00:06:38,550
Is he still living here?

65
00:06:50,920 --> 00:06:51,920
Who are you?

66
00:06:54,159 --> 00:06:54,740
Uh...

67
00:06:56,440 --> 00:06:58,390
Is there a person named Lee Woojin

68
00:06:59,630 --> 00:07:00,740
still living here?

69
00:07:01,120 --> 00:07:02,720
There's no such person here.

70
00:07:29,050 --> 00:07:30,730
The loser pays for snacks.

71
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:32,700
Hurry up!

72
00:08:08,070 --> 00:08:09,070
Let me help you.

73
00:08:49,800 --> 00:08:51,190
This is still here?

74
00:08:58,900 --> 00:08:59,810
I had...

75
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:02,900
a great time today.

76
00:09:04,140 --> 00:09:05,140
Yeah.

77
00:09:07,220 --> 00:09:08,220
Me too.

78
00:09:15,420 --> 00:09:16,300
We're done.

79
00:09:16,740 --> 00:09:19,030
I couldn't have done it alone.

80
00:09:22,170 --> 00:09:24,370
I could only finish it thanks to you too.

81
00:10:53,030 --> 00:10:54,160
What I want to draw?

82
00:10:56,300 --> 00:10:57,360
There is something

83
00:10:57,680 --> 00:10:58,680
I want to draw.

84
00:10:58,900 --> 00:10:59,660
Me?

85
00:10:59,840 --> 00:11:00,900
You want to draw me?

86
00:11:01,170 --> 00:11:02,410
You're the theme for my art.

87
00:11:02,410 --> 00:11:03,610
I want to draw you too.

88
00:11:04,270 --> 00:11:05,270
Then let's draw

89
00:11:06,090 --> 00:11:07,090
our backs.

90
00:11:07,300 --> 00:11:08,800
If I keep it a secret for you,

91
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:09,760
what's in it for me?

92
00:11:09,760 --> 00:11:11,490
Because what's important to me

93
00:11:13,070 --> 00:11:13,860
is you.

94
00:11:14,060 --> 00:11:15,060
Woojin.

95
00:11:15,630 --> 00:11:17,630
Let's stay away
from each other from now on.

96
00:11:17,630 --> 00:11:20,030
What are you talking about,
out of the blue?

97
00:11:21,330 --> 00:11:22,180
We...

98
00:11:25,240 --> 00:11:26,500
must meet again.

99
00:12:51,270 --> 00:12:52,560
Please be alive.

100
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:57,600
Please.

101
00:13:17,450 --> 00:13:18,580
Hey, Jang Hyeseong!

102
00:13:20,470 --> 00:13:21,600
Oh? It's not locked.

103
00:13:27,590 --> 00:13:30,400
Why do you always bang on the door
instead of ringing the bell?

104
00:13:30,400 --> 00:13:32,060
Because it opens when I knock!

105
00:13:32,930 --> 00:13:34,730
Let's have a drink to celebrate.

106
00:13:42,250 --> 00:13:42,980
By the way,

107
00:13:43,610 --> 00:13:46,020
don't forget what you
promised on the phone.

108
00:13:46,020 --> 00:13:46,690
What?

109
00:13:49,440 --> 00:13:51,570
You said you'd give a special lecture.

110
00:13:51,860 --> 00:13:53,870
You wouldn't agree
no matter how I begged you before.

111
00:13:53,870 --> 00:13:55,130
Why the change of mind?

112
00:13:56,050 --> 00:13:56,650
What?

113
00:13:57,570 --> 00:13:59,100
Is it because you heard that

114
00:13:59,100 --> 00:14:01,360
I'd been transferred
to our high school,

115
00:14:01,490 --> 00:14:02,690
the peak of our youth?

116
00:14:04,860 --> 00:14:05,940
What on earth changed

117
00:14:05,940 --> 00:14:07,180
and what didn't?

118
00:14:08,140 --> 00:14:08,900
What?

119
00:14:09,540 --> 00:14:10,520
What changed?

120
00:14:10,850 --> 00:14:11,590
Huh?

121
00:14:11,910 --> 00:14:12,910
No, nothing.

122
00:14:19,350 --> 00:14:20,350
Um...

123
00:14:22,340 --> 00:14:23,950
I have something to ask you.

124
00:14:27,080 --> 00:14:28,010
Woojin...

125
00:14:31,100 --> 00:14:32,320
Uh, what?

126
00:14:36,950 --> 00:14:38,030
How's Lee Woojin?

127
00:14:48,070 --> 00:14:50,670
The wheel of time seems to be
spinning as usual,

128
00:14:52,100 --> 00:14:53,450
but my time

129
00:14:54,640 --> 00:14:56,290
is still stuck on that day.

130
00:15:18,970 --> 00:15:19,970
There's nothing!

131
00:15:30,380 --> 00:15:31,380
Lee Woojin...

132
00:15:34,610 --> 00:15:36,040
Where have you been?

133
00:15:42,740 --> 00:15:47,060
[The Trace of Time]
[Salute to the world of artist Jang Hyeseong]

134
00:15:52,470 --> 00:15:53,600
Hey, Jang Hyeseong!

135
00:15:54,150 --> 00:15:55,640
I knew you'd be late.

136
00:15:55,670 --> 00:15:56,930
Why are you so late?

137
00:15:57,920 --> 00:15:58,920
I had somewhere

138
00:15:58,940 --> 00:15:59,940
to stop by.

139
00:16:00,520 --> 00:16:02,320
Are you sure you didn't sleep in?

140
00:16:03,260 --> 00:16:03,860
All right.

141
00:16:03,980 --> 00:16:05,240
Shall we meet them now?

142
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:07,650
Meet them?

143
00:16:07,720 --> 00:16:08,470
Today will be

144
00:16:08,490 --> 00:16:10,200
another beginning for you.

145
00:16:10,780 --> 00:16:11,780
Get ready.

146
00:16:18,380 --> 00:16:19,380
Another

147
00:16:19,970 --> 00:16:21,070
beginning...

148
00:16:26,160 --> 00:16:26,900
Congratulations.

149
00:16:26,900 --> 00:16:28,060
You're so handsome.

150
00:16:28,390 --> 00:16:29,480
Thank you.

151
00:16:29,780 --> 00:16:30,780
Please smile.

152
00:16:34,290 --> 00:16:35,130
Hello.

153
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:36,860
Congratulations on your exhibition.

154
00:16:36,860 --> 00:16:38,160
Oh. Thank you.

155
00:16:38,320 --> 00:16:39,840
I've been looking forward
to your exhibition.

156
00:16:39,840 --> 00:16:40,670
I'll enjoy it.

157
00:16:40,800 --> 00:16:42,930
Thank you for coming to my exhibition.

158
00:16:49,330 --> 00:16:51,130
Excuse me while I take this call.

159
00:16:56,660 --> 00:16:57,660
Hello?

160
00:17:01,390 --> 00:17:02,520
You didn't find him?

161
00:17:07,730 --> 00:17:08,730
OK.

162
00:17:15,270 --> 00:17:16,119
Mr. Jang.

163
00:17:16,200 --> 00:17:18,270
Can we take a photo with you?

164
00:17:18,380 --> 00:17:19,430
Oh, sure.

165
00:17:19,589 --> 00:17:20,500
Thank you.

166
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:22,520
1, 2, 3!

167
00:17:29,750 --> 00:17:31,350
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

168
00:17:31,360 --> 00:17:32,360
Thank you.

169
00:17:59,270 --> 00:18:00,270
Mr. Jang.

170
00:18:00,780 --> 00:18:01,510
Yes?

171
00:18:01,650 --> 00:18:03,660
You know about the interview, right?

172
00:18:03,660 --> 00:18:04,660
Uh, yes.

173
00:18:05,140 --> 00:18:07,150
I'll come pick you up when you're ready.

174
00:18:07,150 --> 00:18:08,150
OK, thank you.

175
00:18:49,670 --> 00:18:52,520
[Lee Woojin]

176
00:18:51,540 --> 00:18:52,270
Woah.

177
00:18:52,300 --> 00:18:53,300
It's a basketball.

178
00:18:52,540 --> 00:18:55,140
[Lee Woojin]

179
00:18:55,940 --> 00:18:56,730
Thank you.

180
00:18:57,680 --> 00:18:58,680
It's nothing.

181
00:18:58,870 --> 00:19:00,180
How's it nothing?

182
00:19:00,570 --> 00:19:02,570
I can't give you anything like this.

183
00:19:11,970 --> 00:19:14,860
[Lee Woojin]

184
00:19:21,480 --> 00:19:23,610
Mr. Jang, it's time for the interview.

185
00:19:28,640 --> 00:19:29,640
Mr. Jang!

186
00:19:59,420 --> 00:20:00,420
Lee Woojin.

187
00:22:20,920 --> 00:22:21,920
Woojin.

188
00:22:32,400 --> 00:22:33,400
Here.

189
00:22:37,630 --> 00:22:39,560
Hyeseong asked me to give it to you.

190
00:22:43,610 --> 00:22:44,610
Hyeseong?

191
00:22:45,340 --> 00:22:46,050
Yeah.

192
00:22:53,140 --> 00:22:54,140
Hyeseong

193
00:22:55,550 --> 00:22:57,260
always thought of you.

194
00:23:09,400 --> 00:23:10,220
Woojin.

195
00:23:10,870 --> 00:23:12,930
When you read this letter,

196
00:23:13,400 --> 00:23:16,260
I'd have either gone abroad
or vanished for a while.

197
00:23:20,390 --> 00:23:22,790
Sorry for leaving
without saying goodbye.

198
00:23:23,550 --> 00:23:26,060
Every moment I spent with you

199
00:23:26,830 --> 00:23:28,540
was like a gift to me.

200
00:23:29,630 --> 00:23:31,270
I wanted to protect you,

201
00:23:32,350 --> 00:23:34,150
hoping you'll live a happy life.

202
00:23:35,640 --> 00:23:37,240
Even without me by your side,

203
00:23:37,970 --> 00:23:38,970
keep smiling

204
00:23:39,910 --> 00:23:41,270
and keep living well.

205
00:23:42,340 --> 00:23:43,840
If we ever meet again...

206
00:23:45,920 --> 00:23:47,380
No, we will meet again.

207
00:23:48,470 --> 00:23:49,470
Jang Hyeseong.

208
00:23:51,180 --> 00:23:52,730
We must meet again.

209
00:23:54,250 --> 00:23:55,570
When we meet again,

210
00:23:57,250 --> 00:23:58,450
you should smile at me

211
00:23:58,460 --> 00:23:59,790
like nothing happened.

212
00:24:08,420 --> 00:24:09,500
I love you,

213
00:24:09,650 --> 00:24:10,650
Lee Woojin.

214
00:24:11,370 --> 00:24:12,370
From Hyeseong.

215
00:25:48,980 --> 00:25:54,020
[Always Meet Again]

